I"`<p>Magic SysRq key is a key combination which directly provides instructions to the Linux kernel.  Itllows the user to perform various low-level commands regardless of the systemâ€™s state.  It may be used to recover from freezes, allowing the user to reboot a computer without corrupting the filesystem.</p>

